#!/usr/bin/perl
#
# bin/worker/ses-email-events
#
# Worker that processes outbound SES sending events (Delivery, Bounce, Reject,
# Complaint, RenderingFailure) for mail sent through the "dw-prod" SES
# configuration set. Polls an SQS queue fed by SNS from the config set's event
# destination.
#
# Pipeline: SES (dw-prod config set) -> SNS -> SQS -> this worker
#
# This gives per-message visibility into what happens AFTER the SMTP handoff to
# SES, which the dw.email.sent=completed metric does not cover (that only means
# SES accepted the message).
#
# Authors:
#     Mark Smith <mark@dreamwidth.org>
#
# Copyright (c) 2026 by Dreamwidth Studios, LLC.
#
